5 First, we ate here July 16th, which was before the finale of hells kitchen. My wife and I had just gotten married (in Oregon, not Vegas...), and we wanted to treat ourselves to the famed Gordon Ramsay restaurant.  Ambience was great. Dimmed lights, beautiful decorations, and we got a booth with a view of the kitchen. Definitely a romantic feel, which is what I had hoped for being newlyweds. The staff was great. There should be a competition as to who can drink a whole glass of water there before it gets refilled. My wife and I don't go out to nice restaurants very often (she is 2 years out of college, and I'm 86.. j/k, I'm in the military), but we never felt out of place, which I place upon the staff. They were outgoing and attentive, and provided the best service I've ever had. Then the food came... I debated giving them 3 stars for it, but felt the staff earned the 5. The food completely ruined any chance of having a "best steak" (beef wellington) or "best soup" (asparagus soup) anywhere else. Months later and we find ourselves saying, "my steak's really good! Not Gordon Ramsay Steak good, but good!". I wouldn't need teeth to eat the beef wellington. The saying "a knife through warm butter" has been replaced with "a knife through a beef wellington". Don't judge me for my cheesiness there.  All together, way over 5 stars. Best restaurant experience we've ever had, in every area. Will definitely try to dine here again, although it sounds more difficult to get a reservation now (we made ours the day before... but the finale hadn't aired).
