s need to come around more yes?) and service was much better. Food was ALL good...right down to the complimentary free bread with butter and volcanic sea salt. Beef was tender, seafood was cooked to perfection, and OMG the toffee pudding is definitely one of its kind! Even the brussel sprouts had generous giant slabs of high quality bacon.  Overall, food is great, atmosphere is wow, and waiters/servers were nice towards the end...but the attitude I got from the reservations/front desk was not something I'd expect from Gordon Ramsay.
