3 I take an annual pilgrimage to Vegas with my friends for three nights of steak and other ways to kill ourselves early. We decided to see what Mr. Ramsay had for us. The short review is that the food was great, but the service was not very good. We had a 7:30 reservation and showed up at 7:25. We were not seated until 8:20 with no apology or any sort of acknowledgement of our wait. Parties of two came and went while my party of four waited and waited. Once seated we were promptly greeted and drink orders were taken. The drinks took another lifetime to arrive. We were able to order the food, but the apps did not arrive for another 40 minutes. The apps were fine, but we were just hungry at that time. The meat took even longer to arrive, but was served beautifully. I had the Royal Chop which was full of flavor and I did not hesitate to pick up the bone and find the last bits of meat. The sides were well prepared and complemented the meal quite well. The desserts were quite good. I don't typically care for toffee, but the dessert is as advertised. We didn't leave the restaurant until about 11:00 for a 7:30 reservation and it wasn't because we were taking our sweet time. I would certainly come back for the food, but I was left very disappointed with the service and time it took. Yes, it was a Saturday night, but the restaurant was never full at any point.
